OL,7,FTo allow for "greater consistency
OL,8,Facross teams in how non-editorial
OL,9,Fcomplaints are dealt with", the report
OL,10,Fsuggested "better use of technology to
OL,11,Fmanage non-editorial complaints and
OL,12,Fwork to ensure there is a complete
OL,13,Fpicture of all cases across teams
OL,14,Fdealing with them; as well as work to
OL,15,Fensure sufficient resources across
OL,16,Fspecialist teams dealing with non-
OL,17,Feditorial complaints, to manage the
OL,18,Fworkload in a timely manner without
OL,19,Fimpacting on staff welfare".
